===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|田|t1=field|力|t2=strength|ls=ic}} – man providing the strength for agricultural and/or other kinds of (physical) labour on a field.

===Etymology===
Probably an area word. Compare Proto-{{cog|sit-kir}} {{m|und|*nam||man}}, {{cog|mkh-mnc-pro|*k()ɲoom||young child}}, Proto-{{cog|wbm|-}} {{m|und|*h/ʔn[o]m||young man}}, {{cog|th|หนุ่ม||young man; young}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

{{zh-ref|Wang (1982)}} connects it to {{och-l|農|farmer}}. {{zh-ref|Goldin (2021)}} suggests a connection to {{och-l|任|id=2|to bear; to be in charge}}.

